Method Detail

getFactor

int getFactor()
Description copied from interface: Instrument
Returns the factor between the quoted price and the notional value of the handled contract. For example, when requesting to buy 1 Crude Oil future (factor of 1000, or 1000 barrels per contract), valued at 75$ per barrel, the notional amount is 1x1000x$75=$75,000.

This value is typically 1 for stocks and indices. However, it can vary greatly for futures.

This value is not relevant to instruments that are not Tradeable, but it is more convenient for writing a strategy to have it defined in this interface.
